fs.fibu2.view.model
Class FilterPoolModel

java.lang.Object
  fs.fibu2.view.model.FilterPoolModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
YearSeparatorListener, java.util.EventListener, javax.swing.ComboBoxModel, javax.swing.event.ChangeListener, javax.swing.ListModel
public class FilterPoolModel
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.swing.ComboBoxModel, YearSeparatorListener, javax.swing.event.ChangeListener

This class represents the filters available in the FilterPool of a given Journal. Optionally, filters of a certain module can be excluded (e.g. a module usually doesn't want to display its own filters) and standard year filters can be displayed.

Author:
Simon Hampe

Constructor Detail

FilterPoolModel

public FilterPoolModel(Journal journal,
                       JournalModule exclude,
                       boolean yearfilters)
Constructs a new model

Parameters:
journal - The journal from which to take the data. This is essentially used to retrive an instance of FilterPool and to obtain the year filters. If null, a dummy journal is created.
exclude - The module, the filters of which you do not want included in this model. If null, no module is excluded.
yearfilters - Whether the year filters for the corr. journal should be included additionally
